# PM2 Application Deployment and Load Testing on AWS EC2

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to deploy a Node.js application on an AWS EC2 instance using PM2, configure it to run as a background service, scale it using PM2 Cluster Mode, and evaluate its performance under heavy traffic using industry-standard load testing tools.

The primary objective was to understand how a production application behaves under increasing user load, identify performance bottlenecks, and learn how PM2 helps maintain application availability.

---

# Objectives

* Deploy a Node.js application on AWS EC2.
* Manage the application using PM2.
* Configure PM2 as a system service.
* Compare Fork Mode and Cluster Mode.
* Generate traffic using ApacheBench and wrk.
* Monitor CPU and memory utilization.
* Analyze application behavior under heavy load.
* Understand performance limitations and scaling strategies.

