# Project Workflow

## Step 1 – Launch AWS EC2

* Created an Ubuntu EC2 instance.
* Configured Security Groups.
* Opened required ports:

  * 22 (SSH)
  * 3000 (Application)

---

## Step 2 – Install Node.js

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs npm -y
```

---

## Step 3 – Create Express Application

Created a simple Express server that responds to HTTP requests.

```javascript
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
    res.send("Hello from PM2 Demo");
});

app.listen(3000);
```

---

## Step 4 – Install PM2

```bash
sudo npm install -g pm2
```

---

## Step 5 – Start Application

```bash
pm2 start app.js --name demo-app
```

---

## Step 6 – Configure PM2 Startup

```bash
pm2 startup
pm2 save
```

This ensures the application automatically starts after every server reboot.

