# PM2 Fork Mode

Initially the application was deployed in Fork Mode.

Characteristics:

* Single Node.js process
* Limited CPU utilization
* Suitable for development and lightweight workloads

Example:

```bash
pm2 start app.js --name demo-app
```

---

# PM2 Cluster Mode

The application was later migrated to Cluster Mode.

```bash
pm2 delete demo-app
pm2 start app.js -i max --name demo-app
```

Benefits:

* Utilizes all available CPU cores.
* Higher throughput.
* Better fault tolerance.
* Improved concurrency.
* Automatic load balancing across worker processes.

